# Code owners — require a trusted reviewer for the most security-sensitive paths
# (security finding VULN-013). Enforced only when branch protection on `main` has
# "Require review from Code Owners" enabled; this file is the in-repo half.
#
# Last matching pattern wins (GitHub semantics), so order from broad to specific.

# Default owner for everything.
*                           @ersinkoc

# CI/CD and Actions config carry the fork-PR trust gate, SHA pins,
# `permissions: contents: read`, and `persist-credentials: false` (VULN-009).
# A change here can silently weaken every workflow guardrail.
/.github/                   @ersinkoc

# Trust, capability, and execution boundary of the agent runtime.
/kernel/edict/              @ersinkoc
/kernel/runtime/            @ersinkoc
/kernel/warden/             @ersinkoc
/kernel/netguard/           @ersinkoc
/kernel/agentgw/            @ersinkoc
/kernel/redact/             @ersinkoc
/kernel/creds/              @ersinkoc
/kernel/standing/           @ersinkoc
